Class Processor

java.lang.Object
  Adventure.Core.Processor

public class Processor
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to process input from the Player and determine which actions are to be taken based upon the input it has received.

public static java.lang.String directionName(java.lang.String direction)
This method is used to ensure that regardless of whether the key or value for any valid direction is passed in, that only the value will be used. This will allow the Processor to treat "n" and "north" the same (or whatever the case might be).

extractCommands

private static java.lang.String[] extractCommands(java.lang.String lineInput)
This method will take a line of input and convert it into an array of 4 strings that each contain information parsed from the input. The array items will contain: array[0] == Either a verb or a direction will | Always a single word. array[1] == The name of the direct object | Every character until a preposition. array[2] == Whatever preposition is used, if one is. array[3] == The name of the indirect object, if there is one. | The end of the string.

Parameters:
lineInput - The String of input to be parsed.
Returns:
The array of parsed Strings.
